description: Thank you to everyone for coming to the EWeek hype event!!!

Join us for an unforgettable trip down memory lane at the E-Week Hype Event! Fellow mining students will share their favorite moments and cherished memories from past E-Weeks and you get more  about Eweek. Don’t miss the chance to relive the fun and fuel the excitement for next year’s events while enjoying pizza!!

It’s that time of the year to put your pickaxes down, take the shaft up and ignore all the OSHA violations on your way out because it’s time for CMEUS’s Fall banquet 🪖⛏️

Join us at Fisshu on November 21st for an all you can eat sushi dinner (yes you can bring your own wine) with an after party at Cave. 

Attire is formal and tickets include dinner and the after party. 

🚨Tickets are out, link in our bio 🚨

The Fall 2024 mining academic forum will be taking place on Wednesday, November 20th, 2024 at 6pm in FDA 126. This is the perfect time for your voice to be heard and to share feedback with your professors regarding any of your MIME courses. Please rate your courses using the link below (also in the Linktree). All responses are anonymous, so don’t be shy! Pizza will be provided :)

Use the link in our bio to access the form!!

Scenes from the 2023 Mining Fall Banquet. Can’t believe it’s almost been a year! Who else is ready to make more memories? 🍂✨ Mark your calendars because tickets for this fall’s banquet drop TOMORROW at noon. Set those reminders!

Apply apply apply!!! Mining E-week captain applications are out!!

Each team has a max of 6 speaking captains, 3 assistant captains. 

Speaking captains will be in contact with their coord liaison and will consist of 3 speaking captains, minimum 2 e&m captains and 1 rookie captain. 

A link will be available in a few in our bio that you can use to apply. Deadline is the 17th!!!

See you in the mining lounge this week for some free waffles!!
Where?: Mining Lounge
When?: Wednesdays, 9:45 am
Price?: Free if you’re in mining eng -  1$ for 2 waffles if you’re not in mining 

Wooooo!!!!
Hello Mining Students! This November 8th at 5:30 PM in FDA 126 CMEUS presents the biannual MINTALK. Come listen to alumni speak about their career paths after McGill.
